Deployment

psql -d postgres

brew install postgresql

rails new $YOUR_APP_NAME -T --database=postgresql

cd $YOUR_APP_NAME

git init

git add .

git commit -m "Initial commit"

hub create

git push origin master

rails db:create  (use with postgres to create db)

root 'articles#index'  (will go to the home page of the app and not rails)

Heroku need us to define what version of Ruby we are using

ruby '2.3.4' in our gemfile

Istall heroku:  brew install heroku

heroku login

heroku create test-blog

heroku run rails db:migrate

heroku run rails c





